This paper deals with the problem of forming geographical clusters for web-based experiments. It involves the use of anonymized mobile user traffic data to construct a graph representing user movements, which is then clustered to minimize movement between clusters while preserving rough balance in cluster size. This problem involves techniques from several sub-fields of computer science, including social networks (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), databases (cs.DB), spatial databases (cs.SD), and cyber-physical systems (cs.CY).
